<issue_start><issue_comment>Title: vschema user guide doc request
username_0: From @jmoldow:

Can you also discuss the relationship between backups and the recommended max/min/avg/median shard sizes?

Could you possibly also discuss the pros/cons between manually maintaining your keyspace id partitionings, vs. doing an even power-of-2 partitioning? And the kind of scenarios where the former would be required (region sharding, poorly-chosen sharding key with hotspots, etc.)
<issue_comment>username_1: This was mostly addressed by adding: https://vitess.io/docs/user-guides/vschema-guide/

A short note about shard sizes and backups is going to be added to the rule of thumb section here: https://github.com/vitessio/website/pull/897<issue_closed>

<issue_start><issue_comment>Title: Update docs to reflect newly support shells with autocompletions
username_0: * Update Windows docs to use Powershell instead of zsh

Reflect changes made in kubernetes/kubernetes#103758 & kubernetes/kubernetes#92989

I'm not well versed in fish, so I'll leave that part for someone else to get an easy contribution in.
<issue_comment>username_1: adding a /lgtm despite my membership still pending
<issue_comment>username_2: /hold
is this really supposed to be open against dev-1.23?
/cc @jlbutler
<issue_comment>username_1: I appreciated @username_0 s comment that the existing instructions are quite outdated. How about we wrap the new instructions with some sort of version flag?
<issue_comment>username_3: I'm not sure about the branch logistics but powershell and fish won't ship until 1.23 so shouldn't be live before then.
<issue_comment>username_2: that answers my question, thank you!

/milestone 1.23

the hold can be lifted by a reviewer from docs release whenever it's done
<issue_comment>username_0: I've made the changes you've proposed.
<issue_comment>username_1: I have verified the instructions work on Windows Server 2019 and kubectl built from k/k/main
<issue_comment>username_1: I have verified the instructions work on Windows Server 2019 and kubectl built from k/k/main

/lgtm
<issue_comment>username_4: /label tide/merge-method-squash

I've just realized Reuters has shut their feeds down. Lots of good news come from them and I don't want to miss it and it's so sad to see they no longer use RSS. I contacted Reuters to concern about RSS feed and i don't know when they will response to my concern. So yeah, i want to create a bridge but i don't know much about PHP. I got their API right here: 

`https://wireapi.reuters.com/v7/feed/url/{url to each categories}`
Ex: `https://wireapi.reuters.com/v7/feed/url/www.reuters.com/theWire` <-- for 'The Wire' categories
`https://wireapi.reuters.com/v7/feed/url/www.reuters.com/news/technology`  <-- for 'Technology' categories

Feeds based on the categories on their page:
'The Wire',
'Top News',
'Technology News',
'World News',...

<issue_start><issue_comment>Title: Debian Packages in Repo have wrong version for 8u232
username_0: The current 8u232 release's deb version is

1.8.0-232-b09-2

instead of

8u232-b09.openj9-0.17.0-1

That way, debian users won't be able to update, as the new version is treated as old.

Thanks!
<issue_comment>username_1: Yikes. Affects Deb & RPM packages, HotSpot and OpenJ9.
<issue_comment>username_2: @karianna This seems a openjdk-build issue. Would you have the powers to move it there?

<issue_start><issue_comment>Title: 1inch Wallet for IOS listing request 
username_0: 1inch Foundation would like to apply to list the 1inch Mobile Wallet on https://ethereum.org/en/wallets/

The 1inch Labs has released the 1inch Wallet for iOS, which includes the web version’s features and innovative mobile wallet functionality. 

Five major key features that make up the 1inch Wallet:

The best Defi aggregator: Just like the 1inch desktop dApp, the 1inch Wallet offers you access to the most liquidity and the best token swap rates across various DEXes.

Top-level security: All transactions are protected as the wallet parses all data, showing what is happening in a user-friendly manner. Secure Enclave technology enabled by default.

Most liquidity: Users get access to substantial liquidity for swaps across dozens of connected sources. Currently, 50+ sources are available on Ethereum and 20+ on BSC.

Private key and seed phrase scanning: You can easily import wallets by scanning a private key string or seed phrase with a phone camera directly in the app. The feature is powered by AI.

Push notifications: You can approve transactions on your devices, including Apple Watch, without having to log into the 1inch Wallet every time.

Link to the wallet: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/1inch-defi-wallet/id1546049391
<issue_comment>username_1: Hi @username_0 we have a format for suggesting a wallet: [here](https://github.com/ethereum/ethereum-org-website/issues/new?assignees=&labels=Type%3A+Feature%2C+Type%3A+Content&template=suggest_wallet.md&title=)  Please provide all required information in this format, thanks!<issue_closed>
<issue_comment>username_1: Closing due to inactivity. Feel free to reopen with requested info.
